Race 4.



	Habitat of grand canyon which is hot and arid like with some settlements in oasis like areas, work on strata later, maybe with white stone


	Architecture
		À l'extérieure

		Material
			Upper and Middle class have thick stone found locally
			Lower class have a clay based mud covered over small rubble stones which needs a lot of maintenance
			Sun dried brick is very good here.

		Colours
			As light as possible

		Roof
			Flat roof

		Features
			Courtyard (which also acts as a chimney) in the center of the building with lots of plants and water to evaporative cool
			Very thick walls to insulate better
			The length of the building is not faced on the east or west to prevent as much sun exposure
			Wind towers ?

		Windows
			Small and mostly facing the courtyard for cool air, if on the outside will have covers over to prevent direct sunlight, generally avoiding the west and east directions.
			Try to be placed following the wind patterns to maximise the draft

		Room Placements
			 Bedrooms are always on the east


	Culture
		Due to the extremely hot day time, the people are slowly adapting to working in the night, they use natural X which is found underground to light up the place, which are very luminous but quite rare. You may call them nocturnal.
